# Trivy vulnerability suppressions.
#
# Each entry must include a short justification so future reviewers understand
# why the finding is intentionally accepted rather than patched.


# linux-libc-dev kernel CVEs (HIGH/CRITICAL, no upstream fix yet) -- 2026-06-19
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Every entry below is in linux-libc-dev, Ubuntu's kernel-headers package
# pulled in by the build toolchain. They describe host-kernel vulnerabilities;
# a container image cannot patch the running kernel, and Ubuntu has published
# no fixed version (Trivy status "affected", FixedVersion empty). None is in
# an application dependency. The kernel that actually runs is the host's, on
# the host's patch cadence, not this image's headers.
#
# The list was derived from a 24.04 scan; linux-libc-dev is purged from final
# images, so these entries only matter for scans of intermediate layers.
# Re-derive against ubuntu:26.04 if one fires, and drop IDs when Ubuntu
# ships fixes (FixedVersion will populate).
